'''Bail Organa's data holocron''' was a [[Datacron/Legends|data holocron]] that was made by the former [[Senator/Legends|senator]] from [[Alderaan/Legends|Alderaan]], [[Bail Prestor Organa/Legends|Bail Organa]], to store the locations for new bases for the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]], should they ever lose their [[Great Temple/Legends|base]] on [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin 4]]. The data [[Holocron/Legends|holocron]] was encased in [[Phrik/Legends|phrik]], one of the strongest substances in [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]]. When the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|first]] [[Death Star/Legends|Death Star]] [[Destruction of Alderaan/Legends|destroyed]] Alderaan, the data holocron was able to survive the [[Superlaser/Legends|superlaser's]] blast. Shortly after the [[Evacuation of Yavin]], both the Rebel Alliance and the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] discovered that the holocron was floating somewhere in [[the Graveyard]].

The Alliance sent a small [[Fleet/Legends|fleet]], under the command of [[General/Legends|General]] [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]], to the [[Alderaan system/Legends|Alderaan system]] to retrieve the holocron. In turn, the Imperials deployed a fleet of their own and also hired the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]] to find the data holocron. After a small [[Battle of the Graveyard|battle]], the Alliance recovered the holocron and departed the Graveyard. [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Gial Ackbar/Legends|Ackbar]] used the holocron to find [[Boz Pity/Legends|Boz Pity]], a world on the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim]] that would make an ideal base for the Alliance. The Rebels set up a [[Boz Pity base|base]] there until the Empire discovered their location and [[Battle of Boz Pity (Galactic Civil War)/Legends|attacked]] it.

